<function>

access:   public

name: fetchAll

param: string|array, $tags, NULL

param: string, $handle, NULL

param: string|array, $order, NULL

param: int, $page, NULL

return: array

</function>

Fetches a list of bookmarks from the content store.

* Parameters:

 * string|array //$tags//: Fetch bookmarks with all these tags; if empty, fetches for all tags.

 * string //$handle//: The owner_handle (username) to fetch bookmarks for; if empty, fetches for all owners.

 * string|array //$order//: Order in this fashion; if empty, orders by creation-timestamp descending (most-recent first).

 * int //$page//: Which page-number of results to fetch.

* Returns array: The list of bookmarks.

Fetches a list of bookmarks from the content store.

You can specify an owner_handle (username) and/or a list of
tags to filter the list.